node.text:
To celebrate @elijahcraig Old-Fashioned Week, Lynnette Marrero (@drinksat6), bar director of Llama San (@llamasannyc), Llama Inn (@llamainnnyc) and Wonderbar (@wonderbarbeacon), shares how to make her Three Bites of the Apple, an Old-Fashioned inspired by autumn in the Hudson Valley. ⁠
Get the recipe at punchdrink.com and learn more about how you can raise an Elijah Craig Bourbon Old-Fashioned to support the bar community at OldFashionedWeek.com.
#punchpartner @elijahcraig #oldfashionedweek @rwcfusa 
#oldfashioned #cocktail #bartender

Welcome to a special charity episode of “Tip Your Bartender” all about Aperitivo to benefit @rwcfusa! This episode supports industry workers in need by raising funds for @rwcfusa. You can make a contribution by going to the link in our profile, or heading over to @rwcfusa. To date, the Bacardi family of brands has contributed over $150,000 to aid in @rwcfusa’s ongoing relief efforts. @martinirossius will continue their support with a donation following this segment. #raiseyourspirits #drinkpunchtyb

node.text: Have you ever had a Rebujito? The storied, eminently refreshing, Andalusian sherry highball is primed for a breakout. A delicious and complex blend of lemon-lime soda, fino or manzanilla sherry and ice, the populist drink is the stuff of Andalusian legend, fueling hot nights of summer revelry in the Sherry Triangle. As a low-ABV, two-ingredient cocktail with overseas cool factor and endless riffing potential, the Rebujito is ready for its stateside close-up. Head to the link in our profile where @suitcasewine dives into the history of the drink and the bartenders riffing on it today. 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by PUNCH on August 16, 2021 tagging @loirevalleywine. May be an image of food.
Photo by PUNCH on August 15, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: Kümmel is typically found in shaken, citrusy drinks, but @ali.scotch has found a new home for the complex spirit, whose taste he describes as ranging from white chocolate to pink peppercorn to olive tapenade to walnut. Here, he simply stirs it with Campari and aged rum, where the olive flavors from Ron Zacapa 23 complement the caraway and chocolate notes from kümmel. Check out the recipe for The Night Shining via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 15, 2021. May be an image of drink, food and indoor.

node.text: The Mid-Morning Fizz is the perfect summer eye-opener. This RGF variation loses the cream of the original recipe and adds green Chartreuse for a more pronounced spiciness. Light but complex, it's a time-tested hangover cure. Head to the link in our profile for the recipe. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 14, 2021. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text: The Old Haitian is a Mojito, twice removed. @audreysaunders first transformed the classic into an Old Cuban and @orlandofranklin took it one step further. Here, he for opts for clairin, a Haitian rhum agricole, and builds upon it with mint, lime, dry Curaçao and Champagne. Served over crushed ice, rather than up in coupe, it's a summer crusher. Check out the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 14, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, drink and indoor.

node.text: More Melon-Lime Sodas, please. @masanyc's vodka soda with lime x Midori Sour mashup is one of the top-sellers at @katanakitten_nyc for good reason. Head to the link in our profile for the neon green recipe—and tips for building a better highball. #drinkpunch 📷: @ericmedsker

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 13, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: The notion of throwing coconut water into a highball is nothing new. Even in small doses, it adds a characteristic sweet, salty richness to everything from mezcal to rum, and an unparalleled fast track to tropical escapism. From @drinksat6's spin on the Scotch & Coconut to @mauriceshick’s gin-based Wilson, head to the link in our profile for six refreshing, coco-based cocktails to make this weekend. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Please welcome the featured bartenders for the 2021 @tales_of_the_cocktail Foundation Canvas Project presented by @bombaysapphireus (#punchpartner) Applicants for this year’s challenge submitted a 90-second video about their creative passion—from stained glass to woodworking, cross stitching to leather-making and beyond—and 25 talented bartenders were selected from North America. Head to the link in our profile to see the full list.

node.text: There's a spritz out there for everyone, @natashadavidxo is sure of it. “The spritz should be an easy, effortless cocktail—something you can throw together from what you have on hand,” says David. Her "kitchen sink" formula, which has been refined over the course of developing 60+ spritzes for @nitecapnyc, calls for cracked and regular ice cubes, two ounces of wine, one ounce of a low-proof fortified wine, three-quarters of an ounce of something bitter, a teaspoon-measure of fruit liqueur, plus something bubbly. Head to the link in our profile for more on how to build your own spritz. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Choosing the right syrup for your drink shouldn’t be an afterthought. “The role it plays is threefold—syrups not only balance harsh spirits and acids with sweetness, they also lend flavor and add that elusive rich texture on the palate commonly referred to as body.” From simple syrup to honey and agave, @schrammplate’s got your guide to when, and why, to use each. Make yourself a superior sour via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: The "whip shake"—the practice of frothing drinks by shaking with a single ice cube—is the key to the ultra-efficient two-minute Ramos Gin Fizz, a perfectly fluffy pineapple Daiquiri and an expertly diluted Mai Tai. Yet no one seems to know just how the technique entered the modern bartender’s repertoire. Well, *almost* no one. Head to the link in our profile for the story behind the shake. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: The Americano—Campari, sweet vermouth, soda water—is not the first aperitivo that typically comes to mind, but the bittersweet bubbly drink has more to offer than meets the eye. Like all of its Italian cousins, the Americano’s beauty lies in the malleability of its formula—or, more precisely, that it is less a set formula than it is a customizable blueprint. Arrange it however you like, so long as there is a sweet, a bitter and a bubbly component. Head to the link in our profile for six riffs to get you started.  #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro
